caption: Food was awesome!! Will be back!
The Three Little Pig sandwich was amazing! Will definitely be back the next time we're in town. Excellent service too!

We had a delicious brunch of Eggs Benedict over spinach and artichoke and Monte Cristo Crepes. Plus a slice of Quiche Lorraine and mimosas. Great service. Cozy, kitchy decor, which I liked - laid back homey atmosphere. We cleaned our plates and bought a quiche to go. We'll be back.

We ate lunch here as a family and were seated right away. Each of us tried different flavored teas and enjoyed them. Our food was fresh and arrived very quickly to our table. The service could certainly improve, but we would definitely try this place again because the food and teas were so good!
Great little spot for brunch. Great sandwich and soup combo. Friendly staff. Highly recommend.
lovely little brunch place on the square. bottomless coffee and a great lox bagel :)

My wife and I stopped in the Chestnut Tree for breakfast, while passing thru Denton.  We had traditional eggs benedict and smoked salmon benedict.  Both were OUTSTANDING!!!  The facility was very quaint and felt very clean too (during COVID …
It was quiet for our Saturday morning breakfast. All safety precautions appeared to be taken.
Chocolate pie is amazing 👏 😋

Very cute little bistro, we tried many things on the menu, and while everything was delicious the quiche was the absolute best thing we had! Strongly recommend getting the quiche. Our server, who was a gentleman, was very accommodating and made sure our drinks were full!
Certainly a spot worth trying, the food is good and fresh, the cost is reasonable and it is regularly well kept in here. Kudos.

Lovely little place to hangout and look across the square. The service is great and food wonderful. I loved the mini muffins they had at each table and the fresh lemonade. The wall decor inside the restroom was awesome. Loved the hodge-podge recipe sheets all across the walls.

I’m honestly really sad. My boyfriend wanted to try out this place for the first time and the atmosphere is lovely. The coffee was pretty good too. And our waiter was WONDERFUL—that’s mostly why I’m sad, because he was so kind. The food, at …

I love everything about this place. I usually only get to go on Saturdays so I get to catch the mimosa bar and live jazz.  Don't forget to tip these talented musicians!  Update: We absolutely love using the "Marketplace" section on their …
A wonderful and quaint restaurant with a friendly staff.  The Asian Tuna Salad is delicious!

The food was good but my communication with the manager, or lack of communication, while trying to plan an event at this location,  left me very disappointed in this business and would not recommend .
Live music Saturday morning. Food and service usually ver good. Only downside is that parking can be difficult on the square.

Very cozy breakfast and lunch spot. The staff is very friendly and the kitchen is timely but does not sacrifice quality. I've never had to wait here. As a bonus, they often have live jazz music on Saturday mornings. If you go with a big appetite, do yourself a favor and try 'The Dentonite'.
Extraordinary atmosphere and super amiable service. The meals were fresh and yummy. Will clearly recommend this restaurant to anyone. Convenient rates and big portions. Great job.
Food is usually excellent.  Today the chicken Basel quiche tastes like it has been reheated too many times.  Was tough and not fresh
The green chile corn chowder was excellent!
Excellent food and service.
We were in Denton for a convention. We were taken here for lunch. The food was good. We were at a long table against the wall which was awkward.

Good food.. got seated immediately... nice greeter... a bit pricey.. waiter admitted, after a problem with my meal, they're not trained well enough about meal prep to help customers make informed decisions to order.. noticed a similar …
Lovely little spot on the square! Yummy muffins and the best chicken pot pie! We tried different flavors of the tea too- everything was great! Super friendly service as well!
My family and I love the food, service and awesome atmosphere of the Chest Tree.
If you want good bread go, if you’re hungry don’t. The person at the front that took my order was great, I was hungry and wanted a tuna sandwich. Well they forgot to add the tuna
Good food, great service, interesting scenery, and nice people.
Great bistro for family or friends with excellent food.
Terrific vegan chili 🌶
one of my most treasured places in Denton. Go on Saturday and hear the jazz guys. Love this place! I do wish they served coffee, but that’s ok!

Have always wanted to eat brunch here, and now that I have I wonder why it took me so long! I will be back.

Great atmosphere and equally great service!!  Food is delish!
Service was amazing! The food was Awsone! As well as a welcoming, calm environment .

Fantastic food and great people! The food is consistently fantastic! And L-O-V-E the mini-muffins! And the Smoked Salmon Crepes! Abby was our waitress on our most recent visit and she was attentive, but not annoying.

Quaint spot for a mouth watering meal! Delicious menu and a fantastic tea list!

First time in Denton! Visited here with my good friends for brunch!  The atmosphere was relaxing, staff was welcoming, warm, and fun to be around!  The food was fantastic not just in taste but looks as well! I'll be coming here again on my next visit!
Always charming; yummy food.

I have known the owner of this tea room for nearly 30 years, and I just love the chef and restaurant staff--they make you feel like you are a beloved relative visiting in their home. When I have had a tough day at work, I will stop by there …

The food here is great, and they have a range range of tea to choose from.  My only complaint is that I wish they had more “plain” tea options without a bunch of added flavors. Sometime ya just want a solid, normal green tea ya know?

Love this lil spot. Great food selection and the choices I picked were delicious. The staff were all so friendly. The food was served in a very timely manner, even though it was Sunday during brunch. We all made special requests in my party …

Great place, hip, trendy and good food. Will definitely be back!
Good food, consistent service.
Really friendly staff and the eggs are always perfect. They don't mind substitutions and have the best mini muffins made daily.
These wonderful people are so friendly and helpful! We had a last minute after hours event and they were so accommodating.  Thank you for begging willing to work with us!

Great little soup, salad, sandwich place in groovy downtown Denton.
Great little place.

Large selection of Yummy foods. I ordered the vegan chili and chicken salad sandwich. Both were excellent. I am quite impressed with the menu selections, ample portions and quality of food here. I look forward to returning to try something different.

wonderful coffee

Nice little place for breakfast or lunch. It's right on the square so parking may not be super close but it's a great place to eat. The classic ham Benedict was delicious with the breakfast potatoes.

Want to try more of the menu. If you want a glitzy spot, this isn't it. It's down-home and I hope it stays that way.

Not only does this place have great food and staff,  they are also committed to supporting the community. This Thanksgiving they donated food for a dinner to feed the homeless. Thank you for being so awesome!

They have gone downhill since it was sold but its still pretty good. Not as good as before, though.

Great food, friendly staff, awesome atmosphere music and just awesome♡♡

Delicious food served by a friendly waitress. Well worth a visit.
Location, atmosphere,  and service are nice, but in ordering an omelet, the meat was straight out of a 'cold cut deli' packaging (sliced thin) and diced. Step up the quality,  please.
Wonderful food, friendly service, and pretty atmosphere.
Personal favorite of the daytime square eateries. Great quality, friendly staff, very quiet and quaint, even when mostly full. Omelettes, crepes, good brunch stuff.

My waitress was full of personality and made me comfortable. She was very attentive and the food was as good as ever.

Food selection & quality along with quantity are fabulous.  The service was great rhe waitress was very pleasant.  I would recommend this cafe to anyone who travels thru Denton.  Prices are good and the food is great.  Venture out and enjoy

Stop by for lunch with a friend... Had the Mango tea, pork wrap, and pulled pork biscuit with egg(I think that's what it was) and I enjoyed them all.. Friendly staff and great experience.
OMFG BEST VEGAN BREAKFAST IVE HAD IN A LONG TIME!! AND ITS NOT EVEN A VEGAN PLACE!!!!! amazing friendly staff and awesome vibes!!!
Pay for a sample. Stay for the atmosphere.

Excellent food and service!

I recently had the Chesnut Tea Room cater an event and they did a fantastic job at an affordable price. The food was excellent as was the service. Suzanne was a dream to work with. Handled all the details with the facility. Two thumbs up!

The Chestnut tree is always a delight. Whether you want tea or a beer, they've got you covered. A great range of sandwiches, omelets and salad. And their baked goods are a great end to a meal.

Live music and great food. I highly recommend the Asian Tuna salad. I still have dreams at night about eating this meal. I will definitely be dining here again soon. Perfect place to take a date for an early meal on the square.

What a horrible place! HATED! FOOD WAS AWFUL. Even the water tasted funny.  We ordered a chicken club sandwich. We both left the sandwich after the first bite. The service was as bad as the sandwich. What a disappointment. I do have to say, it was the only place in Texas where I had a bad meal.

Quaint, delicious and moderately fast depending on the time of day. I'm a huge tea fan, so I'll sneak in here from time to time for a treat. I also enjoy their lunch menu. There's a good mix of options for both veggies and vegans.
A cafe that knows how to poach an egg.
Not a fan of how hot they keep this place.  Gets uncomfortable when eating.  But always good food and service
Awesome restaurant, great service and I love the Cobb Salad. This is in the square
Don't miss the Saturday brunch starting at 10. Live, professional jazz music (this is, after all, Denton!), great food and great service.
Excellent food, great service, and great live music on Sat. mornings!!
Good food and great service.
Wonderful food and service!! I go here as much as I can! Great cobb salad!!!!

This place is a great brunch spot. Their live music is usually talented, their portion sizes are perfect and the price won't break the bank.

Amazing service and food! Fresh food with large portions and multiple options on bread, cheese, and combinations for the lunch special. This will always be my go to restaurant when we have pharmaceutical reps that bring us lunch!

One of my favorite spots in Denton. Local people, local musicians, specific care to making special food, fresh, quality, with culinary elegance. The servers are happy and friendly and attentive. It's a community feel.

I was delightfully impressed with this place. I will most likely be back here very soon. I came with a friend, it was very busy, but we were seated quickly, and had our drinks in no time. Our food took a little longer than expected, but the …

Service is slow and spotty but the southwest Benedict I had was amazing. Amazing! Now if only it was 12$.... lol

This place not only conveniently located but as soon as u enter you are welcomed with a great introduction of the restaurant with friendly faces and smiles. The food is A+ definitely hit the spot! Try The "Texas turkey panino" will not regret it or exit hungry. Enjoy!

This is a quaint little cafe/bistro on the historic square in Denton.  They have a selection of teas and other drinks along with sandwiches, salads, and baked goods.  Small and inviting this a great place to linger over a cuppa.  The food is good if not exciting, but wholesome and healthy.
I got one of their soups and it was very good! They also serve muffins as you are waiting for their food. 'Nuff said.
All of the food was nice. The staff wasn't rude or too"in your face" just a nice quiet little place to have a tasty meal.

Wow! I forgot my lunch for work and ordered from here on a whim after googling places that deliver to UNT campus. They delivered in 25min and the soup and quiche I ordered were AMAZING! I can't wait to try eating in at the restaurant for my next breakfast or lunch date.
Amazing salad, amazing atmosphere, amazing service!
Best homestyle food in Denton. The pimento cheese, grilled on beer wheat is to die for. Staff is super friendly and the prices are good. Great place to take a lunch date.
